He stressed that it is important to check for the presence of bats before carrying out property maintenance activities, as it is possible that the unintentional destruction of a shelter could kill up to 400 female and young bats, as well as destroy an entire local population.
Bats are a protected species and it is illegal to kill, harass, disturb or destroy their shelters.
